commentary: Lee to Trott, 1 run good god! what a mess that was, terrible cricket all around, both batsmen find themselves at the same end after a huge mix-up, Australia still manage to not get the run-out, Trott blocks the ball from Lee and he's not sure where that went, he turns round to see it round in front of middle stump and has his back to the non-striker as the ball nestles between middle and off stump after rolling gently back, Prior was charging down the track, no idea why he was, Lee races towards the ball, collides with Trott at the batsman's crease, and bowler, batsman and non-striker were all at the striker's end, Lee manages to get the ball after a couple of collisions with Trott, he has loads of time to throw the ball to the other end and get the run-out, he fires in the throw wide though and the fielder at the non-striker's end couldn't collect it and Trott heaves a sigh of relief, as does Prior

commentary: Tremlett to Smith, 2 runs full ball and Smith blazes it towards deep cover where Morgan sprints to his right and dives to make the save. He ball slips out of his grasp as he is sliding but he keeps his calm to grab it again. Terrific effort and the throw back to Tremlett is top class. Tremlett broke the stumps and that was a close run out call. Why didn't anyone appeal? Smith looks short of his ground
